This video made by public health experts from Oxford, Harvard, and Stanford explains how we can still save thousands of lives by switching public policy NOW.

@realDonaldTrump &amp; Governors should listen to these scientists instead of political scientists.

https://t.co/E8NSlFDcEL

@arwest42 I’m wondering if those of us who have antibodies would benefit from exposure to SARS-CoV-2 (or another coronavirus) when our titers are dwindling.

*I’m not advocating this - just questioning!*

Did you have a positive diagnosis of COVID19 or just test positive for antibodies?

@world_diane I’m pretty sure I had it in January, so I feel a bit silly having worn a mask in the months since then.

And I’ve never been anti-N95 mask, just anti-mandates, especially for masks with no specifications or guidance.

Science &gt;&gt; Political_Science
